I"C<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Indeed, it needed several days for us to realize that we were completely <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="cornered"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(被逼入绝境/困住)</code></b>; that words like “special arrangements,” “favor,” and “priority” had lost all effective meaning.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The Prefect sent instructions to Rieux, through Richard, asking him to draw up a <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="minute"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(备忘录)</code></b> to be transmitted for orders to the central administration of the colony. Rieux included in it a clinical diagnosis and statistics of the epidemic.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Thousands of roses wilted in the flower-vender’s baskets in the marketplaces and along the streets, and the air was <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="heavy with"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(充满/满载)</code></b> their <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="\ ˈklȯi-iŋ , ˈklȯiŋ \ disgusting or distasteful by reason of excess"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">cloying</code></b> perfume.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Moreover, the epidemic seemed to be <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="on the wane"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(正在减弱)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>And since, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="in practice"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(实际上)</code></b>, the phrases one can use in a telegram are quickly <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="exhausted"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(用尽/用完)</code></b>, long lives passed side by side, or passionate yearnings, soon declined to the exchange of such trite formulas as: “Am well. Always thinking of you. Love.”</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Thus, for example, a feeling normally as individual as the ache of separation from those one loves suddenly became a feeling in which all shared alike and—together with fear—the greatest affliction of the long period of exile that <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="lay ahead"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(即将来临)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Later on, when these same sentries had had <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="the gravity of the situation"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(事态的严重性)</code></b> <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="drummed into them - (drum sth into sb - 向某人反复灌输)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(灌输到他们体内)</code></b>, they flatly refused to take responsibilities whose possible after-effects they could not foresee.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The telegram <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="ran"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(写道)</code></b>: Proclaim a state of plague stop close the town.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>So we had to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="fall back on"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(退到/求助于)</code></b> telegrams. People linked together by friendship, affection, or physical love found themselves reduced to hunting for tokens of their past communion <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="within the compass of"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(在...的范围内)</code></b> a ten-word telegram.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>In the evening the usual crowd <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="thronged the streets - (throng \ ˈthrȯŋ \ to crowd upon)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(涌上街头)</code></b> and the lines lengthened outside the picture-houses. Moreover, the epidemic seemed to be on the wane; on some days only ten or so deaths were notified.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Cottard <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="went his usual desultory ways - (desultory - \ ˈde-səl-ˌtȯr-ē \ 散漫的/无条理的)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(仍然过着他那散漫的生活)</code></b>, and M. Othon, the magistrate, continued to parade his menagerie.</p>
  </li>
</ol>
